task_description: Facing the building to your West (approx. 280°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the front-left position (10 meters away) will provide a better perspective to view the entire height of the target building from ground to roof, which is necessary for an accurate estimate.
Moving forward to the front position (10.2m away) will bring me closer to the target area, which should help me get a clearer view of the main building for height estimation.
Based on typical residential building floor heights (approx. 3 meters per floor) and observing the building appears to have 6 stories, I estimate its total height to be 18 meters.
